<td VALIGN=TOP bgcolor=ffffff class=itemtable>
<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Vulnerability Loop</div>

<div class=itemtext>Bomb -> Guts -> Cut -> Elec -> Ice -> Fire -> Bomb<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Beginner's Level Orders</div>

<div class=itemtext>This level order starts with Bomb Man, and gives you the proper Master Weapon for all following bosses.
<p>Bomb -> Guts -> Cut -> Elec -> Ice -> Fire
<p>This one starts with the slightly tougher Cut Man, and you'll have to play Elec Man's stage twice, but you'll have more useful weapons early, and you'll have the Magnet Beam for the moving platforms at the start of Guts Man's stage.
<p>Cut -> Elec -> Elec (repeat to get the Magnet Beam) -> Ice -> Fire -> Bomb -> Guts<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Advanced Level Order</div>

<div class=itemtext>If you're planning to use the plasma cannon against most or all of the bosses, this level order wil keep you equipped with the best weapons possible for each level.  As in most Game Boy MM games, this order actually turns out to follow the vulnerability loop.
<p>Guts -> Cut -> Elec -> Ice -> Fire -> Bomb<br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

